overview: The user initiated a request for a significant aesthetic improvement
  of their sleep questionnaire application. The agent began by conducting a
  thorough review of the existing styling, identifying areas such as the generic
  color palette, plain backgrounds, dense form sections, and lack of visual
  personality. The approach involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed
  color palette, enhancing the main form layout with decorative elements and a
  redesigned progress indicator, and overhauling the welcome screen with feature
  cards and improved alerts. All UI components, including checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and cards, were polished for a cohesive look. Crucially, all
  14 questionnaire sections were updated to use the new card-style groupings and
  theme colors, replacing the old gray boxes. During the review, a console error
  related to null values being passed to input fields was identified and fixed
  by modifying the  component to safely handle  values. The
  outcome is a visually appealing, professional, and consistent sleep health
  application.
